    "Subpopulation L2E-2 (southeastern Caspian Sea) contributed 24.7-27.3% to the wheat D genome (Fig. 4a).",
    "Up to 6.9% of the wheat D genome was identical (based on identity-by-state analysis) to Ae.",
    "tauschii subpopulation L2W, with 4.1-5.0% coming from subpopulation L2W-1 and subpopulation L2W-2 contributing 1.7-2.2% (Fig. 4a,b and Extended Data Fig.",
